sentences: Florence Millet (born 1964) is a Franco-German classical pianist who serves as Professor of Piano and Chair of the Piano Department at the Hochschule für Musik und Tanz Köln.
From 1992–2000, Millet played with Ensemble Intercontemporain in Paris under the direction of Pierre Boulez and David Robertson.

Millet was a Fellow at the Tanglewood Music Center from 1988–89 where she received the CD Jackson Award for outstanding achievement by Seiji Ozawa and Leonard Bernstein and was awarded the Florence Gould Fellowship in 1991.
